      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "Main method could also be marked as synchronized, then current behaviour would be the same I think, but I guess for the main method it's easier to notice the usage of lock.\n\nBut one thing for restartApplication(). Now the lock is unlocked before the restart happens, is this intended? I think it would be possible to call restartApplication multiple times, and multiple threads reloading app would run at the same time. Shouldn't the underlying thread hold the lock?",
